  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version: 0.1.0b9\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe documentation states that boolean operations use the common short-circuiting rules. However, the following contract fails at runtime even though the right-hand side of the `and` should not be evaluated at all:\r\n\r\n```\r\ni: int128\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef fail():\r\n    b: bool = self.i != 0 and 1 / self.i == 1\r\n\r\n```\r\nA version with a constant instead crashes at compile time:\r\n\r\n```\r\ni: int128\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef fail():\r\n    b: bool = True or 1 / 0 == 0\r\n```\r\nThe same is true for other operations like underflows of `uint256`.",
